# Cedar Grove Task Tracker — environment variable documentation.
#
# This file lists the variables the app expects. It contains NO real secrets and
# IS committed to git. Copy it to `.env.local` for local development and fill in
# real values there (`.env.local` is gitignored and must never be committed).
#
# On Render, set these in the service's Environment tab — NOT in this file.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# M0 (scaffold): nothing required. The empty app boots with no env vars.
# The variables below are placeholders documenting what later milestones add,
# so Geoff can see what's coming. They are NOT read by any code yet.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# M1 — Database (Postgres on Render, paid plan). REQUIRED from M1 on.
#   The full connection string for Postgres.
#   - On Render: the web service reads this automatically from the database (no
#     manual entry — render.yaml wires it up).
#   - For local development / running migrations from your machine: copy your
#     Render database's "External Database URL" into .env.local as DATABASE_URL.
#   Looks like: postgres://USER:PASSWORD@HOST:5432/DBNAME
# DATABASE_URL=

# M2 — Auth (Clerk). REQUIRED from M2 on. Get these from the Clerk dashboard.
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY is read at BUILD time (it is baked into the
#   browser bundle), so it must be set in Render before/at the build — adding it
#   triggers a rebuild. The other two are server-side runtime secrets.
#   The webhook signing secret comes from the Clerk webhook endpoint you create
#   pointing at <app-url>/api/webhooks/clerk.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
# CLERK_SECRET_KEY=
# CLERK_WEBHOOK_SIGNING_SECRET=

# M6 — Email (Resend) + the daily digest cron.
#   Verify a sending domain before sending to real staff (CLAUDE.md §7).
# RESEND_API_KEY=
# MAIL_FROM="Cedar Grove Tasks <tasks@cedargrovecp.com>"
# CRON_SECRET=                 # shared secret protecting the /api/cron/digest endpoint
# APP_BASE_URL=                # e.g. https://cedar-grove-tasks-staging.onrender.com
